{"questionId":"13244","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The lengths of two of the sides in a triangle are 4 cm and 5 cm. Let <em>θ</em> be the angle between&nbsp;the two given sides. The triangle has an area of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{5\\sqrt {15} }}{2}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>15</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> cm<sup>2</sup>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{{\\sqrt {15} }}{4}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>15</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p><p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{5\\sqrt {15} }}{2} = \\frac{1}{2} \\times 4 \\times 5\\,{\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta \">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>15</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mn>2</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>height of triangle is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{5\\sqrt {15} }}{4}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>15</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;if using 4 as the base or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\sqrt {15} }\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msqrt>\n      <mn>15</mn>\n    </msqrt>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;if using 5 as the base&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{sin}}\\,\\theta&nbsp; = \\frac{{\\sqrt {15} }}{4}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>sin</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>θ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>15</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13244","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_4a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that sin θ = 15 4 .","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig, sine rule, cosine rule, area","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.5—Unit circle definitions of sin, cos, tan. Exact trig ratios, ambiguous case of sine rule"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}